arts.ttl: Bromley keep run going and inflict more misery on Morecambe
Bromley boss always had belief that his players could adapt to League Two football
arts.sum: I won’t allow too many of them but I’ve always been super-positive about this group of players and I think you’ve seen why today.” “If you are a supporter of Bromley, you’ll have been delighted with the effort and commitment and desire that group of players put in,” Woodman said.

Morecambe have lost their last three games and have failed to score in those three games. Bromley's 0-0 draw with Port Vale last weekend extended their unbeaten run to six games and just one defeat i...
